dataLineage.statement:
Administrative boundary lines for Comoros admin level 0-3. Each line is attributed with the highest Admin level that it can represent. These lines can be helpful for cartographic purposes. NOTE: Because Admin1 does not have internal divisions, lines with AdminLevel '99' coastline attribution are also representative of Admin1 boundaries.
An 'AdminLevel' field is used to attribute the lines. The values used for this field are: (0,1,2,3,4,5,99). 99 represents coastline. 0 is international border, 1 is Admin1 border, 2 is Admin2 border, etc. Each line is attributed with the highest admin level that it can participate in.
